f(x)=\begin{cases}x^2-2&,\;\;\text{if}\;\;x=-1\\Ax-4&,\;\;\text{if}\;\;x\neq -1\end{cases}
f(x)
x=-1
\lim_{x \to -1} f(x) = \lim_{x \to -1} (Ax-4) = -A-4
f(-1) = (-1)^2 - 2 = -1
\lim_{x \to -1} f(x) = f(-1)
-A - 4 = -1 \implies A =-3
\lim_{x\rightarrow-1^{-}}{f(x)}=\lim_{x\rightarrow-1^{+}}{f(x)}=f(-1)
f(-1)=(-1)^2-2=-1\Longrightarrow
\,x\to -1\,
\lim_{x\to -1}(Ax-4)=-A-4=-1\Longleftrightarrow A=-3
